1
00:00:07,641 --> 00:00:09,543
Which train should we take?

2
00:00:09,977 --> 00:00:12,446
There's the Keikyu Line, the Monorail,

3
00:00:12,479 --> 00:00:14,081
and buses too!

4
00:00:14,681 --> 00:00:16,183
Mom...

5
00:00:16,650 --> 00:00:20,020
I'm really worried.
You can't even find the right train.

6
00:00:20,053 --> 00:00:22,689
I wish I could pick you up,
but I have to work.

7
00:00:22,723 --> 00:00:25,559
You're the only one we can rely on.

8
00:00:25,592 --> 00:00:29,296
I think we need to take
the Keikyu Line to get to Sis's.

9
00:00:29,329 --> 00:00:30,864
We transfer at Shinagawa.

10
00:00:30,898 --> 00:00:34,001
I think Tami has figured it out.

11
00:00:34,034 --> 00:00:35,569
We'll see you later.

12
00:00:36,603 --> 00:00:38,205
I'm so worried.

13
00:00:38,705 --> 00:00:42,943
I remember being like that too
when I first came to Tokyo.

14
00:00:44,011 --> 00:00:48,849
Can you bring me the new Dior bag
from my desk to the studio downstairs?

15
00:00:48,882 --> 00:00:49,783
Sure thing.

16
00:00:49,816 --> 00:00:53,587
To think I'm working in
the editing department like this.

17
00:00:54,154 --> 00:00:57,758
I, Nami Suzuki,
still make a lot of mistakes.

18
00:00:57,791 --> 00:01:00,527
But my demonic boss
finally said to me...

19
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:01,461
Thank you.

20
00:01:01,495 --> 00:01:03,330
Can you believe it?

21
00:01:03,830 --> 00:01:05,732
My work life and love life are...

22
00:01:08,068 --> 00:01:09,469
Well, my love life is...

23
00:01:09,703 --> 00:01:11,204
I'm in love with you.

24
00:01:12,873 --> 00:01:14,474
Well, it's...

25
00:01:14,875 --> 00:01:18,312
I would never make you cry.

26
00:01:19,046 --> 00:01:19,880
Huh?

27
00:01:20,914 --> 00:01:25,052
But I was being led on
by a puppy-like boy, wasn't I?

28
00:01:25,252 --> 00:01:27,854
But he's more like...

29
00:01:28,956 --> 00:01:30,757
A wild wolf.

30
00:01:30,791 --> 00:01:32,025
Will you go out with me?

31
00:01:33,026 --> 00:01:35,629
Hey, stop it.

32
00:01:35,662 --> 00:01:37,130
Joking around like that.

33
00:01:39,533 --> 00:01:42,436
You don't need to answer me
in a hurry.

34
00:01:48,442 --> 00:01:50,277
Why does Mr. Nakazawa...?

35
00:01:50,844 --> 00:01:54,014
I've done nothing to be loved by him.

36
00:01:56,083 --> 00:01:56,950
What do you want?

37
00:01:57,784 --> 00:01:59,453
Um, nothing.

38
00:02:00,454 --> 00:02:02,723
Was I just dreaming?

39
00:02:03,190 --> 00:02:04,858
Yeah, I must've been.

40
00:02:07,894 --> 00:02:11,031
I was just in a meeting
with the upper echelons.

41
00:02:11,198 --> 00:02:15,669
Sales of the third issue will decide
whether Miyavi can stay in print.

42
00:02:18,472 --> 00:02:19,406
I see.

43
00:02:21,208 --> 00:02:24,044
I'm sorry I couldn't do better.

44
00:02:24,778 --> 00:02:27,447
The merger was already
on the horizon.

45
00:02:27,848 --> 00:02:30,250
So for the two final issues,
forget about sales.

46
00:02:30,484 --> 00:02:33,353
And make the magazine
you've always wanted to make.

47
00:02:39,226 --> 00:02:40,627
Jesus.

48
00:02:41,461 --> 00:02:45,365
Suzuki, Mr. Kato from Armani
is waiting at the entrance.

49
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:49,603
Where are my glasses?
Oh, here they are.

50
00:02:49,703 --> 00:02:51,705
This is still off the record.

51
00:02:51,905 --> 00:02:54,741
But we're planning a new product
in six months.

52
00:02:55,942 --> 00:02:57,177
Six months.

53
00:02:57,210 --> 00:03:00,313
We're hoping to launch
a huge promotion for it.

54
00:03:02,749 --> 00:03:04,017
Leave it to us.

55
00:03:05,752 --> 00:03:07,521
We're going to Valentino now.

56
00:03:08,955 --> 00:03:12,392
I know I'm not in a position to say.

57
00:03:12,793 --> 00:03:15,595
But can't we get Horai Paperworks
to buy ads?

58
00:03:17,330 --> 00:03:19,032
Your father owns it, right?

59
00:03:19,866 --> 00:03:23,703
The status of the magazine
depends on the ads that are in it.

60
00:03:24,704 --> 00:03:29,142
You want to put an ad for tissue
next to some high brands?

61
00:03:31,044 --> 00:03:32,646
But if it were 10,000 yen a sheet...

62
00:03:37,317 --> 00:03:38,518
Just kidding.

63
00:03:39,219 --> 00:03:40,887
I didn't mean that.

64
00:03:40,921 --> 00:03:43,690
That's actually interesting.

65
00:03:47,461 --> 00:03:49,362
Nami

66
00:04:05,045 --> 00:04:05,946
Hey.

67
00:04:07,247 --> 00:04:09,249
I told Suzuki how I feel.

68
00:04:11,685 --> 00:04:15,021
I didn't want to go behind your back,
so I'm telling you.

69
00:04:19,292 --> 00:04:21,394
I'm not going to lose to you. Bye.

70
00:04:23,330 --> 00:04:24,097
Hey.

71
00:04:31,304 --> 00:04:34,641
Is love about winning and losing?

72
00:04:41,948 --> 00:04:44,684
Have you considered my proposal?

73
00:04:44,718 --> 00:04:48,688
Of course.
I can't believe my good luck.

74
00:04:49,189 --> 00:04:51,691
It's all thanks to Reiko.

75
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:55,929
You really hate Ms. Horai.

76
00:04:55,962 --> 00:04:57,497
I don't hate her at all.

77
00:04:58,165 --> 00:05:03,703
I'm just an honest person
who says what I want.

78
00:05:05,071 --> 00:05:08,041
I'm so hungry.

79
00:05:08,375 --> 00:05:13,647
Here, I brought your favorite
red beef rice bowl.

80
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:14,881
Yay!

81
00:05:14,915 --> 00:05:17,017
And mustard lotus roots.

82
00:05:17,050 --> 00:05:19,019
I love mustard lotus roots!

83
00:05:19,052 --> 00:05:20,921
I'm going to go cut some.

84
00:05:21,188 --> 00:05:23,023
- Hey, Nami...
- Tea, right? Hold on.

85
00:05:23,056 --> 00:05:25,192
It's such a nice place.

86
00:05:27,093 --> 00:05:29,062
A lot bigger than I thought.

87
00:05:29,462 --> 00:05:30,664
Here we go.

88
00:05:36,036 --> 00:05:37,170
Honey.

89
00:05:38,004 --> 00:05:40,640
Nami lives here alone, right?

90
00:05:41,608 --> 00:05:43,476
She doesn't live with a boy, does she?

91
00:05:45,845 --> 00:05:49,482
But there are two toothbrushes
over there.

92
00:05:49,950 --> 00:05:52,018
And this was under the bed.

93
00:05:52,052 --> 00:05:53,053
Seriously?

94
00:05:56,056 --> 00:05:59,292
Nami is already 23 now.

95
00:05:59,326 --> 00:06:01,661
What's wrong with
her having a boyfriend?

96
00:06:03,830 --> 00:06:06,199
Maybe she hit it off with Kenchan!

97
00:06:06,900 --> 00:06:09,035
Let's eat.

98
00:06:09,669 --> 00:06:10,570
Here.

99
00:06:16,042 --> 00:06:19,212
- What?
- It's finally happened, huh?

100
00:06:19,246 --> 00:06:23,750
You've finally found
a normal average happy life.

101
00:06:28,321 --> 00:06:29,990
- Somebody's here.
- Who is it?

102
00:06:31,424 --> 00:06:32,792
Could it be...?

103
00:06:33,793 --> 00:06:34,761
Kenchan?

104
00:06:39,866 --> 00:06:40,867
Nami.

105
00:06:56,916 --> 00:07:00,987
Oh My Boss! Love Not Included

106
00:07:01,388 --> 00:07:04,357
I called but you never answered
so I came.

107
00:07:06,126 --> 00:07:07,360
Please leave.

108
00:07:08,228 --> 00:07:09,362
Did I come at a bad time?

109
00:07:09,763 --> 00:07:11,231
You don't know why I'm mad?

110
00:07:12,932 --> 00:07:15,935
I saw you the other day.

111
00:07:17,604 --> 00:07:18,738
You and...

112
00:07:19,906 --> 00:07:21,775
You and Ms. Rio, hugging.

113
00:07:25,845 --> 00:07:28,581
That was just because Rio was sad.

114
00:07:29,783 --> 00:07:30,884
There's nothing...

115
00:07:30,917 --> 00:07:33,753
So you'd hug anybody if they were sad?

116
00:07:35,088 --> 00:07:37,390
Why are you so nice to everybody?

117
00:07:38,925 --> 00:07:42,095
- Well...
- I don't understand you anymore.

118
00:07:44,597 --> 00:07:45,932
What can I do to get you to?

119
00:07:45,965 --> 00:07:48,702
I don't know. Figure it out yourself.

120
00:07:50,403 --> 00:07:51,171
Nami!

121
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:55,942
I won't let you con my daughter!

122
00:07:55,975 --> 00:07:56,776
What?

123
00:07:56,810 --> 00:08:02,082
What's with that fluffy puppy-like
brown hair?

124
00:08:02,115 --> 00:08:03,383
And those piercings.

125
00:08:03,850 --> 00:08:05,852
That fancy coat, too.

126
00:08:06,152 --> 00:08:08,988
I bet you made a girl buy it for you.

127
00:08:09,055 --> 00:08:12,258
Nami already has a man
way better than you.

128
00:08:12,592 --> 00:08:14,160
Now shoo!

129
00:08:14,794 --> 00:08:17,964
- Shoo, shoo!
- I just want to talk with her.

130
00:08:17,997 --> 00:08:19,466
Scram, leave!

131
00:08:20,300 --> 00:08:22,936
My parents are here from Kumamoto.
Have some.

132
00:08:22,969 --> 00:08:24,070
Thanks.

133
00:08:24,371 --> 00:08:25,705
- Thanks.
- It's good.

134
00:08:25,739 --> 00:08:27,307
- Here.
- Thank you.

135
00:08:28,408 --> 00:08:30,510
Mr. Handa, have one.

136
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:33,480
I can only stomach jelly right now.

137
00:08:34,547 --> 00:08:36,116
- Just jelly.
- Suzuki.

138
00:08:36,149 --> 00:08:37,183
Are you free tomorrow?

139
00:08:38,651 --> 00:08:40,286
I, um... Tomorrow?

140
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:43,356
Yeah, to cover a cottage up in Nagano.

141
00:08:44,124 --> 00:08:46,126
Oh right, work.

142
00:08:46,393 --> 00:08:48,828
Huh? Just the two of us?

143
00:08:49,195 --> 00:08:50,330
Are you free or not?

144
00:08:50,363 --> 00:08:52,432
Huh? Um...

145
00:08:53,066 --> 00:08:56,603
I have... Ms. Horai wants me tomorrow.

146
00:08:57,237 --> 00:08:58,104
Okay.

147
00:08:58,538 --> 00:09:00,206
I'll go with you.

148
00:09:00,540 --> 00:09:01,307
What for?

149
00:09:01,875 --> 00:09:04,244
To make some final memories.

150
00:09:04,778 --> 00:09:08,114
How about it everyone,
let's go to Shirahimegawa.

151
00:09:08,148 --> 00:09:10,283
I have to prepare
for next week's shoot.

152
00:09:10,316 --> 00:09:12,185
Finish that up today.

153
00:09:12,218 --> 00:09:13,153
Everyone got it?

154
00:09:13,186 --> 00:09:14,120
I have a family mass.

155
00:09:14,621 --> 00:09:15,855
- Me too.
- Me too.

156
00:09:15,889 --> 00:09:17,390
All of you?

157
00:09:17,424 --> 00:09:19,526
As if that would happen.

158
00:09:19,559 --> 00:09:23,196
Listen up, we're all going tomorrow
on a day camp.

159
00:09:24,497 --> 00:09:25,265
Suzuki.

160
00:09:26,199 --> 00:09:27,233
Get me a taxi.

161
00:09:28,968 --> 00:09:30,670
Thank you for the material.

162
00:09:31,471 --> 00:09:33,940
What are you up to now?

163
00:09:34,474 --> 00:09:36,543
I'm looking for a big client.

164
00:09:39,279 --> 00:09:41,047
Isobe Inc.

165
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:46,219
"Isobe has successfully developed
a new sericin extraction technology."

166
00:09:46,252 --> 00:09:50,089
"With it, they developed
a new silk skin lotion."

167
00:09:50,123 --> 00:09:51,257
You want their ad on Miyavi?

168
00:09:52,392 --> 00:09:54,694
It's a small company
with only 200 employees.

169
00:09:56,296 --> 00:09:57,564
That's right.

170
00:09:58,031 --> 00:10:01,267
That look, I know it.

171
00:10:02,502 --> 00:10:04,604
It's the devil's grin.

172
00:10:06,039 --> 00:10:07,073
Suzuki.

173
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:08,308
Yes!

174
00:10:08,341 --> 00:10:10,677
I want to make a call tomorrow.

175
00:10:12,078 --> 00:10:14,113
I need you to do something for me.

176
00:10:14,481 --> 00:10:15,582
Sure thing.

177
00:10:16,082 --> 00:10:17,817
- Got it?
- This one?

178
00:10:17,851 --> 00:10:19,786
Yeah, that's perfect.

179
00:10:19,819 --> 00:10:21,855
Mr. Jun, you have a visitor.

180
00:10:22,188 --> 00:10:23,890
A real hottie too.

181
00:10:30,797 --> 00:10:31,698
Here.

182
00:10:32,832 --> 00:10:33,766
Thanks.

183
00:10:35,134 --> 00:10:35,902
What is it?

184
00:10:38,738 --> 00:10:41,007
I wanted to apologize
about the other day.

185
00:10:41,374 --> 00:10:42,175
About what?

186
00:10:45,445 --> 00:10:48,081
I hadn't told anyone about my hand.

187
00:10:49,148 --> 00:10:50,817
I was on my own the whole time.

188
00:10:53,653 --> 00:10:56,089
So, sorry for crying.

189
00:10:57,323 --> 00:10:58,258
Oh, that.

190
00:11:04,430 --> 00:11:07,300
So, have you gotten the results yet?

191
00:11:10,236 --> 00:11:11,638
The day after tomorrow.

192
00:11:15,842 --> 00:11:16,743
Hey, Jun?

193
00:11:18,344 --> 00:11:20,046
Can you come with me?

194
00:11:21,748 --> 00:11:23,783
I'm scared of going by myself.

195
00:11:28,888 --> 00:11:29,822
Sure.

196
00:11:31,891 --> 00:11:32,559
Really?

197
00:11:40,466 --> 00:11:41,534
Never mind.

198
00:11:42,902 --> 00:11:43,803
Why?

199
00:11:44,204 --> 00:11:45,371
Oh jeez.

200
00:11:46,773 --> 00:11:50,109
You're always nice,
and I always take advantage of you.

201
00:11:52,145 --> 00:11:55,882
Being nice to everyone
isn't nice to anybody.

202
00:12:01,454 --> 00:12:03,156
I actually still love you.

203
00:12:05,358 --> 00:12:06,626
I love you, Jun.

204
00:12:09,095 --> 00:12:10,363
I still do.

205
00:12:15,635 --> 00:12:18,905
But I put an end to that years ago.

206
00:12:20,907 --> 00:12:22,475
And I want to root for Nami.

207
00:12:24,944 --> 00:12:25,979
So...

208
00:12:28,414 --> 00:12:29,182
So...

209
00:12:32,385 --> 00:12:34,420
When you're nice to me...

210
00:12:36,389 --> 00:12:37,357
it hurts.

211
00:12:43,963 --> 00:12:47,700
Gosh, that must hurt for Mr. Jun too.

212
00:12:48,735 --> 00:12:52,872
Wow, this is where Kenchan lives?

213
00:12:52,905 --> 00:12:55,341
I'm so proud of my future son-in-law.

214
00:12:55,375 --> 00:12:57,610
You better find yourself
an accountant too.

215
00:13:02,015 --> 00:13:03,182
Why are you here?

216
00:13:05,018 --> 00:13:07,387
Kenchan? Who is that?

217
00:13:08,388 --> 00:13:09,656
She's, um...

218
00:13:09,689 --> 00:13:11,491
Are they your fiancée's parents?

219
00:13:11,858 --> 00:13:13,559
- Damn.
- Be quiet.

220
00:13:13,593 --> 00:13:14,994
What's going on?

221
00:13:15,528 --> 00:13:17,463
Are you cheating on her?

222
00:13:17,997 --> 00:13:20,333
Please forget what you saw here!

223
00:13:21,067 --> 00:13:22,235
I can't lose my job.

224
00:13:22,268 --> 00:13:25,104
What about Nami, huh?

225
00:13:25,438 --> 00:13:27,173
Aren't you sorry for her?

226
00:13:27,206 --> 00:13:29,275
Nami doesn't matter, but my job...

227
00:13:29,308 --> 00:13:30,777
I can't believe you!

228
00:13:36,683 --> 00:13:39,819
I have to work tomorrow.

229
00:13:40,553 --> 00:13:43,389
Sorry I can't
show you guys around Tokyo.

230
00:13:44,857 --> 00:13:47,260
You can't help it.

231
00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:51,264
Don't be so depressed.

232
00:13:51,297 --> 00:13:53,599
I'll be free Sunday, okay?

233
00:13:54,834 --> 00:13:57,970
So hey, Nami?

234
00:13:58,204 --> 00:13:59,739
If you want,

235
00:14:00,073 --> 00:14:05,511
you can come back home to Kumamoto
anytime you want.

236
00:14:05,845 --> 00:14:08,081
That's absolutely right, dear.

237
00:14:08,514 --> 00:14:09,782
Why?

238
00:14:09,816 --> 00:14:11,217
We should tell her.

239
00:14:11,484 --> 00:14:12,385
You're right.

240
00:14:14,087 --> 00:14:15,021
Nami.

241
00:14:15,488 --> 00:14:18,224
You have a boyfriend, don't you?

242
00:14:20,126 --> 00:14:23,062
Dad noticed the two toothbrushes.

243
00:14:23,396 --> 00:14:25,565
Oh, um yeah.

244
00:14:25,598 --> 00:14:28,101
I'm really sorry.

245
00:14:28,134 --> 00:14:30,737
I know we shouldn't have done it.

246
00:14:30,770 --> 00:14:32,939
But we went to his apartment.

247
00:14:32,972 --> 00:14:34,741
To his apartment?

248
00:14:34,774 --> 00:14:37,910
We just thought we'd say hello.

249
00:14:37,944 --> 00:14:38,811
No way...

250
00:14:38,845 --> 00:14:42,181
He came outside
with a short-haired girl.

251
00:14:43,483 --> 00:14:44,884
A short-haired girl?

252
00:14:46,119 --> 00:14:48,020
Jun, let's go on a walk.

253
00:14:52,391 --> 00:14:56,696
I don't need a leash.
I'll never wander from you.

254
00:14:58,064 --> 00:14:58,865
Jun...

255
00:15:03,970 --> 00:15:05,772
I knew it.

256
00:15:07,473 --> 00:15:11,978
I thought it'd be better you knew
rather than continue the relationship.

257
00:15:14,247 --> 00:15:16,582
Yeah, I get it.

258
00:15:19,118 --> 00:15:21,554
I had a feeling about it too.

259
00:15:22,688 --> 00:15:25,057
What? You knew?

260
00:15:32,031 --> 00:15:34,834
- We're here!
- Feels amazing.

261
00:15:34,867 --> 00:15:37,203
- You ate too many tangerines.
- Huh?

262
00:15:37,236 --> 00:15:38,704
Suzuki?

263
00:15:38,738 --> 00:15:40,373
Why are you here?

264
00:15:40,406 --> 00:15:42,308
What are you doing here?

265
00:15:42,341 --> 00:15:45,211
Oh, you're all here
to cover that cottage.

266
00:15:46,112 --> 00:15:50,316
I'm here with Ms. Horai
to call on a potential client.

267
00:15:50,783 --> 00:15:51,918
Must be tough, huh.

268
00:15:52,351 --> 00:15:54,987
But you see, I saw it.

269
00:15:56,155 --> 00:15:58,925
Ms. Horai's devil's grin.

270
00:15:58,958 --> 00:16:00,393
You mean it?

271
00:16:00,426 --> 00:16:02,495
When Reiko Horai smiles, it means...

272
00:16:03,095 --> 00:16:04,130
Money will start rolling.

273
00:16:05,064 --> 00:16:08,301
When you're done,
join us and report what happened.

274
00:16:08,334 --> 00:16:09,535
Got it.

275
00:16:10,136 --> 00:16:11,270
Okay, let's go.

276
00:16:11,604 --> 00:16:13,606
- Later.
- Bye.

277
00:16:21,647 --> 00:16:22,682
Suzuki.

278
00:16:22,715 --> 00:16:25,418
I'm picking up a gift,
so you go on ahead.

279
00:16:28,921 --> 00:16:30,690
But the next bus is in an hour.

280
00:16:30,723 --> 00:16:31,991
Okay, then.

281
00:16:42,902 --> 00:16:44,003
Do you need help?

282
00:16:49,075 --> 00:16:50,977
Now shoo!

283
00:16:51,010 --> 00:16:53,446
I just want to talk with her.

284
00:16:56,249 --> 00:16:57,183
Are you...

285
00:16:59,051 --> 00:17:00,987
I'm going to need a ruler for this.

286
00:17:02,521 --> 00:17:03,723
I'll go buy a ruler.

287
00:17:06,425 --> 00:17:08,127
But...

288
00:17:08,928 --> 00:17:11,097
Otowado is about to go under.

289
00:17:11,130 --> 00:17:14,100
I wasn't of any help.

290
00:17:14,333 --> 00:17:17,069
You need to figure out
how you really feel.

291
00:17:17,970 --> 00:17:20,439
Oh no, it's gone.

292
00:17:20,473 --> 00:17:21,874
Let's find a place to stay.

293
00:17:30,249 --> 00:17:32,084
Is that so?

294
00:17:32,318 --> 00:17:34,787
So you're Sis's boyfriend?

295
00:17:34,820 --> 00:17:37,423
Wow, he's so puppy-like.

296
00:17:37,456 --> 00:17:39,292
Now stop that.

297
00:17:39,892 --> 00:17:44,597
I always thought
Nami had been dating Kenchan.

298
00:17:44,630 --> 00:17:49,035
I'm so sorry about the other day.

299
00:17:50,002 --> 00:17:51,971
No, that's okay.

300
00:17:52,305 --> 00:17:56,776
Now that I can see you better,
you're really quite handsome.

301
00:17:56,809 --> 00:17:58,511
So white!

302
00:17:59,445 --> 00:18:00,246
Where is Nami?

303
00:18:00,846 --> 00:18:06,185
Oh you see, she suddenly had to go
to Nagano for work.

304
00:18:06,218 --> 00:18:07,553
Says her boss is the devil.

305
00:18:08,688 --> 00:18:09,522
I know.

306
00:18:12,892 --> 00:18:15,061
We're here!

307
00:18:15,094 --> 00:18:16,629
Feels amazing.

308
00:18:16,662 --> 00:18:18,297
Hey, we can fish here.

309
00:18:18,698 --> 00:18:19,498
Let's fish!

310
00:18:19,532 --> 00:18:21,167
I gotta go work.

311
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:23,169
Such a goody-two-shoes.

312
00:18:23,202 --> 00:18:24,103
I'll help.

313
00:18:24,604 --> 00:18:26,572
- What kind of fish are there?
- Thanks.

314
00:18:26,606 --> 00:18:29,442
We're not here just to have fun.

315
00:18:30,843 --> 00:18:33,512
Otowado is about to go under.

316
00:18:34,880 --> 00:18:36,315
I heard them talking.

317
00:18:36,549 --> 00:18:38,417
Ms. Horai and Mr. Ugajin.

318
00:18:38,451 --> 00:18:40,686
Do you have to tell us that now?

319
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:45,157
But not anymore since
Ms. Horai smiled her devil's grin.

320
00:18:45,858 --> 00:18:49,261
If all goes well,
we might pull through.

321
00:18:50,997 --> 00:18:55,001
Go, go, Ms...

322
00:18:58,204 --> 00:19:00,873
I think she'll be here shortly.

323
00:19:01,974 --> 00:19:03,943
Maybe she missed the bus.

324
00:19:04,977 --> 00:19:07,279
I can send somebody to go pick her up.

325
00:19:07,313 --> 00:19:08,881
No, that's fine.

326
00:19:09,849 --> 00:19:11,350
I'm going to go call her.

327
00:19:15,221 --> 00:19:16,756
Where are you right now?

328
00:19:17,089 --> 00:19:18,557
- Ginza.
- Ginza?

329
00:19:18,858 --> 00:19:19,725
Yes.

330
00:19:20,159 --> 00:19:21,560
But this is Nagano.

331
00:19:21,594 --> 00:19:23,129
I need you to do something.

332
00:19:23,896 --> 00:19:27,466
Keep him entertained
until I get there.

333
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:28,367
Bye.

334
00:19:31,771 --> 00:19:33,005
Seriously?

335
00:19:38,911 --> 00:19:40,379
I'm so sorry.

336
00:19:41,213 --> 00:19:42,848
She'll be here soon...

337
00:19:45,918 --> 00:19:49,255
I mean, she's going to take a while.

338
00:19:52,091 --> 00:19:55,127
Let me sing you a song!

339
00:19:58,130 --> 00:19:59,331
Just kidding.

340
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:05,404
Wow, it's so huge.

341
00:20:05,938 --> 00:20:10,910
Thank you so much
for showing us around Tokyo.

342
00:20:10,943 --> 00:20:12,912
I had the day off today.

343
00:20:13,312 --> 00:20:15,915
I'll take a picture for you.

344
00:20:22,888 --> 00:20:24,523
Okay, smile.

345
00:20:33,232 --> 00:20:34,400
Where is everyone?

346
00:20:41,373 --> 00:20:42,608
That's the charged area.

347
00:20:52,151 --> 00:20:55,154
Which should I choose? This one!

348
00:21:05,397 --> 00:21:07,666
- Got it.
- Thank you.

349
00:21:11,937 --> 00:21:13,005
Be careful.

350
00:21:18,410 --> 00:21:22,982
He gathered every rock in the village
and put them in Hikoichi's farm.

351
00:21:23,015 --> 00:21:28,220
But Hikoichi didn't get mad.
He said so the raccoon could hear,

352
00:21:29,455 --> 00:21:32,024
"What great luck!"

353
00:21:32,057 --> 00:21:36,862
"If this had been horse's manure,
I would've..."

354
00:21:36,896 --> 00:21:38,597
Excuse me.

355
00:21:39,331 --> 00:21:42,168
I think that's enough for today.
Maybe another time.

356
00:21:43,202 --> 00:21:45,137
Can we have just a little more time?

357
00:21:45,171 --> 00:21:49,975
I'm sure you big magazines from Tokyo
have better clients you can deal with.

358
00:21:50,009 --> 00:21:50,943
Ms. Horai must be busy.

359
00:21:50,976 --> 00:21:53,045
She'll be here shortly, so please!

360
00:21:53,078 --> 00:21:55,247
- Look...
- Please.

361
00:21:56,081 --> 00:21:57,750
I know.

362
00:21:58,951 --> 00:22:01,020
Have you ever heard of this story?

363
00:22:21,307 --> 00:22:22,441
Ms. Horai!

364
00:22:23,509 --> 00:22:25,211
Ms. Horai!

365
00:22:32,151 --> 00:22:35,955
I'm honored that you've taken notice
of our skin lotion.

366
00:22:36,488 --> 00:22:37,756
But you see,

367
00:22:38,123 --> 00:22:43,195
we don't have the funds
to buy an ad in a top class magazine.

368
00:22:43,929 --> 00:22:46,465
And even if we did,

369
00:22:46,498 --> 00:22:52,171
we'd be alongside brands like
Louis Vuitton, Cartier, and Gucci.

370
00:22:52,972 --> 00:22:57,876
Nobody would notice our ad
next to those big names.

371
00:22:58,811 --> 00:23:02,815
Then how about branding your company
to be as big as the others?

372
00:23:03,382 --> 00:23:04,583
Branding?

373
00:23:04,617 --> 00:23:10,022
For example, it'd be strange to have
a tissue ad next to Gucci.

374
00:23:11,423 --> 00:23:13,792
But not if it's tissue by Dior.

375
00:23:14,426 --> 00:23:17,763
That's what I said the other day.

376
00:23:18,464 --> 00:23:22,434
With the popularity and trust
of high brands and your technology,

377
00:23:23,235 --> 00:23:25,237
combined with our platform,

378
00:23:25,771 --> 00:23:29,942
it wouldn't be impossible
to conquer the world.

379
00:23:30,442 --> 00:23:35,047
It would've been nice to hear this
if you'd arrived on time.

380
00:23:37,616 --> 00:23:41,320
I had wished to prepare
the perfect gift for you.

381
00:23:41,987 --> 00:23:45,090
And it took longer than expected.
I apologize.

382
00:23:45,391 --> 00:23:46,959
What gift, huh?

383
00:23:47,793 --> 00:23:50,929
An agreement to a contract with Coach.

384
00:23:58,270 --> 00:24:02,608
Coach has agreed to do a collaboration
with your skin lotion.

385
00:24:03,475 --> 00:24:06,645
Coach normally doesn't do lotions.

386
00:24:07,212 --> 00:24:09,048
This will be
a special limited product.

387
00:24:11,583 --> 00:24:16,455
I wished to bring this to you today,
and negotiated with Coach.

388
00:24:16,955 --> 00:24:19,024
So that's why you were late?

389
00:24:19,725 --> 00:24:24,363
They said you shared the same passion
towards technology.

390
00:24:25,431 --> 00:24:27,299
And agreed to this project.

391
00:24:28,600 --> 00:24:31,837
I will be awaiting your answer.

392
00:24:37,009 --> 00:24:38,177
Excuse us.

393
00:24:49,221 --> 00:24:52,257
- Tea?
- They just left.

394
00:24:52,291 --> 00:24:53,325
Oh really.

395
00:24:55,761 --> 00:25:00,265
That lady walked all the way here
from the station.

396
00:25:00,766 --> 00:25:01,967
In those heels.

397
00:25:06,705 --> 00:25:07,473
I'm back.

398
00:25:08,374 --> 00:25:09,174
Hi.

399
00:25:11,310 --> 00:25:13,112
How did the business meeting go?

400
00:25:14,279 --> 00:25:15,814
Still no answer yet.

401
00:25:16,248 --> 00:25:17,950
What will our destiny be?

402
00:25:18,517 --> 00:25:20,419
I'm going to buy some drinks.

403
00:25:21,019 --> 00:25:22,020
Want anything?

404
00:25:22,054 --> 00:25:23,055
I'll go and choose.

405
00:25:23,489 --> 00:25:25,991
- Mr. Handa?
- Green tea.

406
00:25:27,559 --> 00:25:30,262
Ms. Haruka, will you go with him?

407
00:25:36,735 --> 00:25:37,636
Ms. Suzuki.

408
00:25:39,571 --> 00:25:40,572
Can we talk?

409
00:25:43,409 --> 00:25:46,311
I need you to stop doing that.

410
00:25:47,379 --> 00:25:48,881
Makes me feel pitied.

411
00:25:53,218 --> 00:25:56,121
Is it because
you don't want to be alone with him?

412
00:25:56,388 --> 00:25:58,590
Or because you're being nice to me?

413
00:25:58,991 --> 00:26:00,793
Either way, you're avoiding him.

414
00:26:02,161 --> 00:26:04,062
- I...
- I saw it.

415
00:26:05,431 --> 00:26:07,065
I'm in love with you.

416
00:26:09,201 --> 00:26:12,004
I would never make you cry.

417
00:26:18,410 --> 00:26:23,549
If you think
you might like Mr. Nakazawa...

418
00:26:24,550 --> 00:26:25,617
then tell him yes.

419
00:26:28,220 --> 00:26:32,291
Who do you love?
Who do you want to be with forever?

420
00:26:34,927 --> 00:26:37,763
You need to figure out
how you really feel.

421
00:26:40,999 --> 00:26:43,569
It's almost time to return the car.
Let's go.

422
00:26:45,537 --> 00:26:47,072
All right then.

423
00:26:48,173 --> 00:26:50,342
I had so much fun.

424
00:26:50,876 --> 00:26:53,712
- So refreshing.
- I'm going to be so sad.

425
00:26:54,213 --> 00:26:56,415
Suzuki? What's wrong?

426
00:26:58,851 --> 00:27:00,118
My bracelet...

427
00:27:00,419 --> 00:27:01,587
You lost it?

428
00:27:01,887 --> 00:27:02,788
What's wrong?

429
00:27:03,188 --> 00:27:04,456
Nothing.

430
00:27:05,824 --> 00:27:08,160
This will bring you good luck.

431
00:27:15,334 --> 00:27:19,605
I'm going to look for it,
so you guys go ahead to the station.

432
00:27:19,771 --> 00:27:21,540
- Really?
- Are you sure?

433
00:27:21,573 --> 00:27:23,275
I'll be fine, I'll take the bus.

434
00:27:23,775 --> 00:27:26,512
There aren't a lot running,
so be careful.

435
00:27:42,561 --> 00:27:43,962
I was over there, so...

436
00:27:59,177 --> 00:27:59,978
Hey.

437
00:28:02,247 --> 00:28:04,316
You better hurry
or we'll miss the bus.

438
00:28:06,552 --> 00:28:07,586
Mr. Nakazawa.

439
00:28:26,204 --> 00:28:29,041
Nakazawa texted and said
they'll take the next train.

440
00:28:31,176 --> 00:28:33,679
Which bento do you want?

441
00:28:33,946 --> 00:28:36,381
Thank you!

442
00:28:37,015 --> 00:28:39,918
Beer? But I still have to work.

443
00:28:47,693 --> 00:28:48,527
Found it?

444
00:28:50,162 --> 00:28:50,996
My phone is dying.

445
00:29:04,810 --> 00:29:05,978
We looked enough.

446
00:29:07,613 --> 00:29:08,947
Thank you.

447
00:29:10,782 --> 00:29:12,117
But it's important to you.

448
00:29:14,620 --> 00:29:15,854
It's from him, isn't it?

449
00:29:18,690 --> 00:29:19,825
But it's okay.

450
00:29:22,961 --> 00:29:24,463
It's too late anyways.

451
00:29:27,633 --> 00:29:28,400
The bus!

452
00:29:28,433 --> 00:29:29,234
Shoot!

453
00:29:31,203 --> 00:29:34,039
Oh no, it's gone.

454
00:29:37,976 --> 00:29:39,611
The next bus is in an hour.

455
00:29:40,646 --> 00:29:42,514
We'll miss the last train.

456
00:29:43,248 --> 00:29:44,282
Damn it.

457
00:29:46,518 --> 00:29:47,686
Oh well.

458
00:29:48,620 --> 00:29:50,055
Let's find a place to stay.

459
00:29:59,297 --> 00:30:01,333
Thanks, Junnosuke.

460
00:30:01,867 --> 00:30:05,971
We really enjoyed Tokyo,
all thanks to you.

461
00:30:06,204 --> 00:30:10,042
Lucky Sis, having such
a kind boyfriend like you.

462
00:30:10,075 --> 00:30:12,210
Normal and nice, nothing beats that.

463
00:30:14,746 --> 00:30:15,714
Um...

464
00:30:16,882 --> 00:30:18,617
Am I nice?

465
00:30:19,151 --> 00:30:20,752
- Yeah.
- Very.

466
00:30:21,019 --> 00:30:21,953
Really nice.

467
00:30:25,323 --> 00:30:29,895
But being nice to everybody
ends up hurting somebody.

468
00:30:33,265 --> 00:30:37,636
Is that why you and Nami
were fighting the other day?

469
00:30:41,740 --> 00:30:43,709
Yes, we have a room available.

470
00:30:43,742 --> 00:30:45,911
We'd like separate rooms.

471
00:30:45,944 --> 00:30:49,281
I'm sorry, but we only have
one available room.

472
00:30:49,614 --> 00:30:51,349
Is that okay?

473
00:30:53,985 --> 00:30:56,154
Okay, that's fine.

474
00:30:56,188 --> 00:30:57,222
Of course.

475
00:30:58,023 --> 00:30:58,924
Suzuki.

476
00:31:00,092 --> 00:31:02,828
You stay here by yourself.
I'll find somewhere else.

477
00:31:03,228 --> 00:31:04,663
- But...
- I'll be fine.

478
00:31:05,130 --> 00:31:08,667
Can I leave my stuff with you?
It's too heavy to lug around.

479
00:31:12,204 --> 00:31:14,873
Later.
I'll come get it in the morning.

480
00:31:15,741 --> 00:31:18,710
The room is bigger than I thought.

481
00:31:19,111 --> 00:31:20,045
We can sleep apart.

482
00:31:20,512 --> 00:31:23,682
Or we can borrow cards
and play until morning.

483
00:31:23,715 --> 00:31:24,483
Suzuki.

484
00:31:29,488 --> 00:31:33,291
If you were my girlfriend...

485
00:31:34,926 --> 00:31:38,430
I wouldn't want you spending the night
with some other guy.

486
00:31:43,001 --> 00:31:43,769
Later.

487
00:31:45,137 --> 00:31:46,304
Mr. Nakazawa.

488
00:31:50,575 --> 00:31:51,376
Um...

489
00:31:54,880 --> 00:31:56,348
I need to give you an answer.

490
00:31:59,584 --> 00:32:00,652
Tell me in the morning.

491
00:32:03,255 --> 00:32:05,323
Can you wait till morning?

492
00:32:06,758 --> 00:32:07,225
Okay?

493
00:32:07,626 --> 00:32:08,460
Yeah.

494
00:32:14,533 --> 00:32:16,635
That was so yummy.

495
00:32:16,668 --> 00:32:19,171
Tokyo's Chinese food is amazing.

496
00:32:23,208 --> 00:32:26,812
You're right,
if you're nice to everybody,

497
00:32:26,845 --> 00:32:29,948
there may be times
where you hurt someone.

498
00:32:31,349 --> 00:32:35,487
But if it weren't for you,
we'd be stuck in Nami's room all day.

499
00:32:35,520 --> 00:32:38,390
We wouldn't have been able
to see Tokyo.

500
00:32:38,590 --> 00:32:43,161
But you showed us around
the whole day.

501
00:32:43,361 --> 00:32:46,298
And we've created
such wonderful memories.

502
00:32:47,866 --> 00:32:50,302
All thanks to your kindness.

503
00:32:53,605 --> 00:32:56,942
Being kind to everyone and anyone

504
00:32:56,975 --> 00:32:58,844
isn't something anybody can do.

505
00:32:59,311 --> 00:33:05,383
I'm sure that's what Nami
loves about you too.

506
00:33:07,886 --> 00:33:09,387
You think so?

507
00:33:10,155 --> 00:33:11,556
I think so too.

508
00:33:14,059 --> 00:33:15,360
Junnosuke.

509
00:33:15,861 --> 00:33:16,561
Yes?

510
00:33:16,795 --> 00:33:18,330
Please.

511
00:33:21,733 --> 00:33:23,134
Take care of Nami for us.

512
00:33:24,336 --> 00:33:27,272
Yes, please do.

513
00:33:29,241 --> 00:33:30,108
Yes.

514
00:33:37,749 --> 00:33:40,118
Oh? Junnosuke?

515
00:33:41,086 --> 00:33:42,254
You're Nami's senpai.

516
00:33:42,287 --> 00:33:44,823
Kazumi. Remember that.

517
00:33:45,156 --> 00:33:46,224
Waiting for Suzuki?

518
00:33:47,259 --> 00:33:48,960
She's not coming back today.

519
00:33:49,661 --> 00:33:51,930
- Nagano?
- Yeah, Shirahimegawa.

520
00:33:51,963 --> 00:33:54,299
I got a text from Nakazawa.

521
00:33:54,332 --> 00:33:57,836
Said they both missed the last train.

522
00:33:57,869 --> 00:33:59,404
So stupid, huh?

523
00:33:59,437 --> 00:34:00,705
I'm not holding back.

524
00:34:01,072 --> 00:34:02,807
They went to an inn together.

525
00:34:03,241 --> 00:34:06,111
But we're back here working and...

526
00:34:50,388 --> 00:34:53,124
You should refrain
from wearing heels for a while.

527
00:34:54,025 --> 00:34:55,193
Mr. Ugajin.

528
00:34:56,094 --> 00:34:58,830
Shall I treat it for you?

529
00:34:59,130 --> 00:35:01,266
I'm a certified doctor.

530
00:35:03,868 --> 00:35:04,636
Just kidding.

531
00:35:07,005 --> 00:35:08,707
Don't work yourself too hard.

532
00:35:10,442 --> 00:35:11,676
Thank you.

533
00:35:19,651 --> 00:35:21,152
I change my mind. Will you please?

534
00:35:23,888 --> 00:35:24,689
Does that hurt?

535
00:35:25,657 --> 00:35:26,558
It's okay.

536
00:35:34,766 --> 00:35:36,167
I'm sorry.

537
00:35:39,137 --> 00:35:42,941
I wasn't of any help.

538
00:35:43,708 --> 00:35:44,476
No.

539
00:35:45,343 --> 00:35:47,278
You did so much for us.

540
00:35:48,480 --> 00:35:52,050
Never mind the results.
You are a wonderful woman.

541
00:36:02,727 --> 00:36:04,596
Editor-in-chief of Miyavi
Reiko Horai

542
00:36:19,444 --> 00:36:21,446
15 missed calls from Junnosuke

543
00:36:28,887 --> 00:36:34,559
Sorry, I told Junnosuke that you and
Nakazawa were staying the night.

544
00:36:34,592 --> 00:36:35,960
Should I not have?

545
00:36:40,265 --> 00:36:42,167
I'm not doing anything wrong.

546
00:36:47,739 --> 00:36:51,009
Junnosuke was with Rio too, so there.

547
00:37:00,952 --> 00:37:02,921
Stop calling me!

548
00:37:03,354 --> 00:37:05,123
I'm not your boyfriend.

549
00:37:06,391 --> 00:37:07,392
Mom?

550
00:37:07,425 --> 00:37:11,296
We're going home to Kumamoto
tomorrow morning.

551
00:37:11,830 --> 00:37:12,730
I'm sorry.

552
00:37:13,698 --> 00:37:16,801
I couldn't show you around Tokyo
at all.

553
00:37:16,801 --> 00:37:20,238
Not at all.
We got to see you doing well.

554
00:37:20,572 --> 00:37:22,373
And your boyfriend, too.

555
00:37:23,675 --> 00:37:26,878
Junnosuke, he's your boyfriend, right?

556
00:37:27,412 --> 00:37:29,748
He showed us around Tokyo today.

557
00:37:30,281 --> 00:37:31,916
What, why?

558
00:37:31,950 --> 00:37:35,453
We were so wrong.

559
00:37:35,920 --> 00:37:38,523
We thought you were dating Kenchan.

560
00:37:39,390 --> 00:37:44,295
The boy we saw with
the short-haired girl was Kenchan.

561
00:37:45,497 --> 00:37:47,465
Really?

562
00:37:47,832 --> 00:37:52,570
Junnosuke came every day
hoping to see you.

563
00:37:53,204 --> 00:37:57,242
What a nice boy, like a little puppy.

564
00:37:58,076 --> 00:37:59,811
It took me back.

565
00:38:00,445 --> 00:38:03,348
Back to when I first started
dating your father.

566
00:38:04,115 --> 00:38:06,050
You never told me about that.

567
00:38:06,818 --> 00:38:11,022
I was so in love with your father.

568
00:38:11,656 --> 00:38:15,160
I heard he was going to Tokyo
to become a writer.

569
00:38:15,193 --> 00:38:19,264
And I stopped him and shouted,
"Don't go!"

570
00:38:19,464 --> 00:38:21,032
And we started dating.

571
00:38:21,599 --> 00:38:25,937
Those words were the beginning
of all my troubles.

572
00:38:28,606 --> 00:38:29,908
But you know what?

573
00:38:30,542 --> 00:38:35,413
When you were born,
and when Tami was born,

574
00:38:35,780 --> 00:38:40,084
and when I first met your boyfriend,

575
00:38:40,952 --> 00:38:45,223
I really felt it was all thanks
to those words that I said.

576
00:38:48,426 --> 00:38:53,898
I told your father how I truly felt.

577
00:38:53,932 --> 00:38:55,700
And I'm glad I did.

578
00:38:59,170 --> 00:39:02,473
Well, stay healthy and keep it up!

579
00:39:19,424 --> 00:39:21,192
How I truly feel...

580
00:39:21,759 --> 00:39:22,827
Nami.

581
00:39:23,695 --> 00:39:24,796
I love you.

582
00:39:25,063 --> 00:39:26,464
Let's stay together forever.

583
00:39:30,134 --> 00:39:34,806
Junnosuke was always the one
that said how he felt.

584
00:39:36,040 --> 00:39:39,010
I always complained about
how he led me on.

585
00:39:39,777 --> 00:39:42,046
But I'd never told him how I felt.

586
00:39:42,880 --> 00:39:47,919
And that's the only reason
I felt like I was being thrown around.

587
00:39:54,048 --> 00:40:00,955
Morning! Can we have dinner tonight?
I miss you. Can we meet? Call me.

588
00:40:01,388 --> 00:40:05,392
I need to talk to you.
I'll be waiting at 9 PM by your office.

589
00:42:21,347 --> 00:42:22,282
This is Horai.

590
00:42:22,782 --> 00:42:24,584
About your proposal yesterday.

591
00:42:26,019 --> 00:42:27,353
I'd like to do it.

592
00:42:27,787 --> 00:42:28,922
Wonderful.

593
00:42:29,722 --> 00:42:30,957
Thank you.

594
00:42:50,043 --> 00:42:50,877
Kotaro!

595
00:43:39,192 --> 00:43:40,527
Kotaro, that's his name?

596
00:43:42,428 --> 00:43:44,530
Good for you, Kotaro.

597
00:43:47,734 --> 00:43:48,801
Junnosuke.

598
00:43:51,504 --> 00:43:52,438
Why...?

599
00:43:54,207 --> 00:43:55,174
Nami.

600
00:43:56,809 --> 00:43:58,411
So this is where you were.

601
00:44:00,880 --> 00:44:02,448
I get it now.

602
00:44:03,116 --> 00:44:06,019
You brought me here, huh Kotaro?

603
00:44:07,053 --> 00:44:09,088
What a good little boy.

604
00:44:10,490 --> 00:44:11,724
Thanks.

605
00:44:21,467 --> 00:44:24,170
Wait, you're bleeding.

606
00:44:24,904 --> 00:44:26,472
I fell off my bike.

607
00:44:26,906 --> 00:44:27,941
Oh no.

608
00:44:37,517 --> 00:44:39,519
Your hands are so small.

609
00:44:43,790 --> 00:44:49,729
The whole time I was riding my bike,
I thought about you.

610
00:44:53,533 --> 00:44:57,337
My heart pounds really fast
when I think about you.

611
00:44:58,438 --> 00:45:00,707
I'm happy when you laugh.

612
00:45:01,574 --> 00:45:03,109
I'm sad when you cry.

613
00:45:05,845 --> 00:45:08,081
And you're the only one
in the whole world

614
00:45:09,649 --> 00:45:11,851
that makes me feel that way.

615
00:45:14,988 --> 00:45:16,289
Junnosuke.

616
00:45:23,696 --> 00:45:25,365
Now it's my turn.

617
00:45:27,033 --> 00:45:28,101
Can I say how I feel?

618
00:45:33,573 --> 00:45:35,141
I want you all to myself.

619
00:45:36,776 --> 00:45:38,945
I want you to look at me only.

620
00:46:15,548 --> 00:46:17,450
I only have eyes for you.

621
00:46:26,559 --> 00:46:28,061
Don't cry.

622
00:46:36,035 --> 00:46:37,937
Neurosurgery

623
00:46:41,774 --> 00:46:43,409
Ms. Hasumi, come in.

624
00:46:45,645 --> 00:46:46,312
Yes.
